introduction: The Respiratory Virus Hospitalization Surveillance Network (RESP-NET) comprises three platforms that conduct population-based surveillance for laboratory-confirmed hospitalizations associated with COVID-19, Influenza, and Respiratory Syncytial Virus (RSV) among children and adults.
title: Respiratory Virus Hospitalization Surveillance Network (RESP-NET) Content Implementation Guide
desc: This is the initial ballot release of the RESP-NET FHIR IG.
